{
  "skillId": "substitute-into-expressions",
  "atomType": "R",
  "theory": {
    "intro": "To **substitute** means to replace each pronumeral with a given number; to **evaluate** means to work out the result using the order of operations.",
    "facts": [
      "**Substitute** by replacing every pronumeral with its value, written in **brackets**: when $x = 3$, the expression $4x$ becomes $4(3)$.",
      "**Evaluate** using the order of operations — **powers**, then **× and ÷**, then **+ and −**.",
      "A power binds to the **pronumeral only**: $2x^2$ means $2 \\times x \\times x$, not $(2x)^2$.",
      "The same pronumeral takes the **same value** everywhere it appears."
    ],
    "steps": [
      "Substitute each value in brackets.",
      "Work out powers.",
      "Multiply and divide.",
      "Add and subtract."
    ]
  },
  "practice": {
    "foundation": [
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $3x$ when $x = 4$.",
        "solution_text": "$3x$\n$= 3(4)$\n$= 12$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $x + 8$ when $x = 5$.",
        "solution_text": "$x + 8$\n$= (5) + 8$\n$= 13$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $2x + 5$ when $x = 3$.",
        "solution_text": "$2x + 5$\n$= 2(3) + 5$\n$= 6 + 5$\n$= 11$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $12 - 2x$ when $x = 4$.",
        "solution_text": "$12 - 2x$\n$= 12 - 2(4)$\n$= 12 - 8$\n$= 4$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $\\frac{x}{3}$ when $x = 15$.",
        "solution_text": "$\\frac{x}{3}$\n$= \\frac{15}{3}$\n$= 5$"
      }
    ],
    "development": [
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $3a + 2b$ when $a = 6$ and $b = 4$.",
        "solution_text": "$3a + 2b$\n$= 3(6) + 2(4)$\n$= 18 + 8$\n$= 26$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $pq$ when $p = 6$ and $q = 4$.",
        "solution_text": "$pq$\n$= (6)(4)$\n$= 24$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $x^2 + 3x$ when $x = 3$.",
        "solution_text": "$x^2 + 3x$\n$= (3)^2 + 3(3)$\n$= 9 + 9$\n$= 18$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $\\frac{5c - 7}{2}$ when $c = 3$.",
        "solution_text": "$\\frac{5c - 7}{2}$\n$= \\frac{5(3) - 7}{2}$\n$= \\frac{15 - 7}{2}$\n$= \\frac{8}{2}$\n$= 4$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $40 - 4x$ when $x = 8$.",
        "solution_text": "$40 - 4x$\n$= 40 - 4(8)$\n$= 40 - 32$\n$= 8$"
      }
    ],
    "mastery": [
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $2x^2$ when $x = 4$.",
        "solution_text": "$2x^2$\n$= 2(4)^2$\n$= 2(16)$\n$= 32$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $x^2 + 3x - 4$ when $x = 3$.",
        "solution_text": "$x^2 + 3x - 4$\n$= (3)^2 + 3(3) - 4$\n$= 9 + 9 - 4$\n$= 14$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Evaluate $2d - 3e - 4f$ when $d = 2$, $e = 3$ and $f = \\frac{1}{2}$.",
        "solution_text": "$2d - 3e - 4f$\n$= 2(2) - 3(3) - 4(\\frac{1}{2})$\n$= 4 - 9 - 2$\n$= -7$"
      }
    ]
  }
}
